@LoganOxenham appreciation post.

Over the past few months I’ve had the pleasure to get to know Logan as he campaigned in the recent by-election. He performed super well and came within a razor’s edge of taking away a safe seat from the PC government who were running a star candidate.

Logan did this by focusing on the people of the riding. While others were talking about themselves Logan was listening to the people of Kirkfield-Park, where he lives with his family, and putting forward common sense solutions to help them.

I look forward to the future because after this strong result I have no doubt, if we stay humble and focused, Logan will be working with our team for many years to come!

The federal government should take a step back, listen to Manitobans and withdraw this C-21 amendment.

We are 100% committed to caring for seniors in Manitoba. Seniors have been taking a backseat for far too long.
We will balance the budget with a real plan to grow our economy, create jobs and invest in families with a broad middle class tax cut and not raising the PST.

Yesterday, I was proud to stand next to @wabber as he announced the @ndpmanitoba vision to balance the books while balancing the diverse needs of the province.

If we win government, we will eliminate waste by working directly with school divisions to provide your tax relief. We will freeze your hydro rates. We will reduce taxes for the middle class. 

Bottom line: We will be on YOUR side when it comes to the cost of living.

In Manitoba, the PC’s have handed cheques to billionaires, froze wages of working people, and hiked Hydro, MPI, and tuition rates - all after forcing international students and workers to pay medical bills of up to $500,000. 

A government that gives handouts to billionaires and a Premier that forgets about $31 million doesn’t understand how regular families are struggling.

We deserve better. Wab Kinew and the Manitoba NDP are promising better.
